                    "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10983872/distance-from-a-point-to-a-polygon/57267222#57267222",
                    "body": "<p>I do not know about the difference in performance with respect to the rest of answers, but in boost C++ libraries there is an generic implementation called <a href=\"https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_57_0/libs/geometry/doc/html/geometry/reference/algorithms/distance/distance_2.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">distance</a>. It has information about complexity in every case and in your problem case it is linear.</p>\n\n<p>I was also looking for solutions to this problem some days ago and I want to share this finding. Hope it helps to someone.</p>\n"
